        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 6 at 4:58PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 458 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 5 miles southeast of Lightning Flat, or 42 miles
southeast of Broadus, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lightning Flat and New Haven.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
